2. **Deploy**: Fork this repo ‚Üí Connect to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) ‚Üí Add DATABASE_URL ‚Üí Deploy
3. **Initialize**: Visit `/api/init-db` after deployment

### Option 2: Render + Supabase
1. **Database**: Sign up at [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) ‚Üí Create project ‚Üí Copy connection string
2. **Deploy**: Fork this repo ‚Üí Connect to [render.com](https://render.com) ‚Üí Add DATABASE_URL ‚Üí Deploy

## üõ†Ô∏è Technologies

- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Radix UI
- **Backend**: Express.js, Node.js, PostgreSQL
- **Database**: Drizzle ORM with type-safe queries
- **State Management**: TanStack Query
- **Notifications**: Chrome Notifications API
- **Charts**: Recharts for data visualization

## üìä Key Features

### Attendance Calculation
- **Class-based tracking**: Counts individual classes, not days
- **Percentage calculation**: Real-time attendance percentage
- **Goal analysis**: Determines if target percentage is achievable
- **Trend visualization**: Charts showing attendance patterns

### Notification System
- **Daily reminders**: Customizable reminder times
- **Goal alerts**: Notifications when attendance drops below target
- **Weekly reports**: Summary of attendance progress
- **Browser notifications**: Works on desktop and mobile Chrome

### Schedule Management
- **Weekly schedules**: Define classes for each day of the week
- **Time slots**: Specific start and end times for each class
- **Holiday support**: Mark holidays to exclude from calculations
- **Recurring patterns**: Set up semester-long schedules

## üîß Development

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Set up environment variables
DATABASE_URL=your_postgresql_connection_string

# Run development server
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Start production server
npm start
